# Test on Change Strategy

Run tests in tiers based on scope. Fix failures before proceeding—you have the best context immediately after making a change.

## Tier 1: After Modifying a File

Run related unit tests only:

```bash
# Backend: run tests matching the module
npx vitest run tests/unit/modules/<module-name>.*.spec.ts

# Example: after editing src/modules/auth/auth.service.ts
npx vitest run tests/unit/modules/auth.service.spec.ts
```

## Tier 2: After Completing a Feature/Fix

Run affected e2e tests:

```bash
# Run e2e tests for the feature area
npx vitest run tests/e2e/<feature>.e2e.spec.ts

# Example: after auth changes
npx vitest run tests/e2e/auth.e2e.spec.ts
```

## Tier 3: Before Commit/PR

Run quick validation:

```bash
npm run qa:monster:quick
```

## If Tests Fail

1. Fix immediately—don't move on with broken tests
2. Re-run the failing test to confirm the fix
3. Then continue to the next tier

## Skip Conditions

- Documentation-only changes: skip all tiers
- Config/env changes: skip to Tier 3
- Pre-existing failures: note them, don't block on unrelated issues
